    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="58"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/1992: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-08">undated</date>.<lb/>[Received
                        April 9, 1940—12:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Foreign Minister<note n="12" xml:id="d58fn12">Halvdan Koht.</note> informs me
                    the Norwegians have fired on four German warships coming up Oslofjord, and that
                    Norway is at war with Germany! Five warships are also en route Bergen.</p>
                <p>British Minister requests us to take over his Legation in case he is obliged to
                    evacuate. Cannot reach you by telephone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
